reviewText:
Despite not being a fan of super heroes, this game is a superb title. Amazing game!

Injustice: Gods Among Us Ultimate Edition is one of the best fighting games I've ever played, and I've played a few!

I will be comparing this to one of my favourite fighting games, Mortal Kombat Komplete Edition, which was also made by NetherRealm Studios.
Injustice brings new mechanics to the table, such as throwing random objects (such as barrels and monitors) found in the different stages at your opponent, and some stage (not all though) changes when you hit your opponent hard enough into one of the corners. Also, your health bar doesn't refill after winning a round. Combat has also been improved, much faster and fluid combos, and different blocking controls.

But there's also stuff missing. In this title you can only fight 1vs1, you don't have the tag-team fights which Mortal Kombat has.

The rest, I'll just make a list with Pros & Cons to make it simple.

Pros:
Amazing graphics and dynamic lighting;
30 fighters to choose from;
Interactable and a decent number of stages;
Decent story mode;
Very neat menus;
Lots of fighting to do;
In-depth combat but simple controls;
Lots of costumes;
Glorious animations;
XP based levelling system (for unlockables, etc);
Scorpion!
Cons:
No tag-team battles;
Everything is unlocked from the start (except for the icons, backgrounds and badges)**In my opinion, it takes away the joy of unlocking new costumes and other stuff.


I haven't really tried the multiplayer online, so I can't express my feelings on it. But the local multiplayer is a joy, the fighting is very fun and addictive when having a friend on the same skill level as you are.

I'm sure there is more positive stuff and probably some bad stuff too, but I can't seem to remember any right now.

All in all, this game is very, very good! If you're a fan of fighting games like me, you are definitely going to enjoy this title, and if you're into super heroes, then you absolutely MUST get it!
It is well worth the full price, but if you catch it on sale, well... Even better!
